Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the @rigatoni pasta{180%g}.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved and sliced into thin strips) and discard the core and seeds. 

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

When the water is boiling, add the rigatoni to the pan and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} to the pan and season with @salt and @pepper. Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Once browned, transfer the chicken to a #small bowl{}.

Pop the (now empty) frying pan back on high heat (no need to clean). Add another drizzle of oil (if needed).

Add the sliced pepper and onion to the frying pan. Stir in the @sugar{1%tsp}, then season with salt and pepper. Stir fry until the veg has softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once softened, add the browned chicken back into the frying pan, along with the @Mexican style spice mix{1%sachet} and the garlic. Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Next, stir the @water{1.5%tbsp} and @chicken stock paste{10%g} into the chicken.

Bring to the boil and simmer until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the sauce has reduced, stir in the @soured cream{150%g} and the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}. Season with salt and pepper, then bring to the boil then simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Add the pasta to the sauce and stir together to combine.

Taste and add more salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little dry.

Share the fajita style pasta between your bowls. Enjoy!

> A customer favourite, this Creamy Fajita Style Chicken Breast Pasta is a tried-and-tested recipe that always wins with a crowd.